Description: Ostracon, large fragment of the shoulder section of buff pottery vessel, interior and exterior slightly grooved, with faint traces of two lines of black-painted hieratic text on the exterior identifying contents as year 11 wine of the domain of Neferneferuaten (Nefertiti) from the western river branch of the Delta.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amarna, el-, TA:21-22/169 Workmen's Village
Curator's comments: Peet & Woolley, City of Akhenaten I:164 pl.LXIII, fig.I
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393125) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393125)
Associated places: Named in inscription: Domain of Neferneferuaten
